    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, slice your <strong>cucumber </strong>finely into discs</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped dill </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and set aside to pickle – this is your <strong>dill quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
